Roman Renaissance</em> (Manchester Medieval Studies), Manchester, UK:
Manchester University Press. doi:10.7765/9781526109514</li>

<li>O&rsquo;Meara, Dominic J., 2003, <em>Platonopolis: Platonic
Political Philosophy in Late Antiquity</em>, Oxford: Clarendon.
doi:10.1093/acprof:oso/9780199285532.001.0001</li>

<li>Orwin, Alexander I., 2015, &ldquo;Democracy under the Caliphs:
Alfarabi&rsquo;s Unusual Understanding of Popular Rule&rdquo;, <em>The
Review of Politics</em>, 77(2): 171&ndash;190.
doi:10.1017/S0034670515000029</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2017, <em>Redefining the Muslim Community:
Ethnicity, Religion, and Politics in the Thought of Alfarabi</em>,
Philadelphia, PA: University of Pennsylvania Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash; (ed.), 2022, <em>Plato&rsquo;s Republic in
the Islamic Context: New Perspectives on Averroes&rsquo;s
Commentary</em> (Rochester Studies in Medieval Political Thought),
Rochester, NY: University of Rochester Press.</li>

<li>Ottaviani, Didier, 2018, <em>La naissance de la science politique:
autour de Marsile de Padoue</em> (Politiques 16), Paris: Classiques
Garnier.</li>

<li>Parens, Joshua, 1995, <em>Metaphysics as Rhetoric:
Alfarabi&rsquo;s Summary of Plato&rsquo;s &ldquo;Laws&rdquo;</em>
(SUNY Series in Middle Eastern Studies), Albany, NY: State University
of New York Press.</li>

<li>Pines, Shlomo, 1957, &ldquo;Notes on Averroes&rsquo; Political
Philosophy / &#1500;&#1495;&#1511;&#1512;
&#1514;&#1493;&#1512;&#1514;&#1493;
&#1492;&#1502;&#1491;&#1497;&#1504;&#1497;&#1514; &#1513;&#1500;
&#1488;&#1489;&#1503; &#1512;&#1493;&#1513;&#1491;&rdquo;, <em>Iyyun:
The Jerusalem Philosophical Quarterly</em>, 8(2): 65&ndash;84. Article
in Hebrew.</li>

<li>Quillet Jeannine, 1979, &ldquo;L&rsquo;aristot&eacute;lisme de
Marsile de Padoue et ses rapports avec l&rsquo;Averro&iuml;sme&rdquo;,
<em>Medioevo</em>, 5: 81&ndash;142.</li>

<li>Robinson, Jonathan, 2013, <em>William of Ockham&rsquo;s Early
Theory of Property Rights in Context</em> (Studies in Medieval and
Reformation Traditions 166), Leiden/Boston: Brill.
doi:10.1163/9789004245730</li>

<li>Rosenthal, Erwin I. J., 1953, &ldquo;The Place of Politics in the
Philosophy of Ibn Rushd&rdquo;, <em>Bulletin of the School of Oriental
and African Studies</em>, 15(2): 246&ndash;278.
doi:10.1017/S0041977X00111103</li>

<li>Sherman, Claire Richter, 1995, <em>Imaging Aristotle: Verbal and
Visual Representation in Fourteenth-Century France</em>, Berkeley, CA:
University of California Press.</li>

<li>Shogimen [Sh&#333;gimen], Takashi, 2007, <em>Ockham and Political
Discourse in the Late Middle Ages</em> (Cambridge Studies in Medieval
Life and Thought. Fourth Series 69), Cambridge: Cambridge University
Press. doi:10.1017/CBO9780511497223</li>

<li>Stocchi-Perucchio, Donatella, 2017, &ldquo;Dante Politico: Toward
a Mapping of Dante&rsquo;s Political Thought&rdquo;,
<em>Mediaevalia</em>, 38: 13&ndash;36.</li>

<li>Strauss, Leo, 1935, <em>Philosophie und Gesetz: Beitr&auml;ge zum
Verst&auml;ndnis Maimunis und seiner Vorl&auml;ufer</em>, Berlin:
Schocken.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1952, &ldquo;The Literary Character of the
<em>Guide for the Perplexed</em>&rdquo;, in <em>Persecution and the
Art of Writing</em>, Glencoe, IL: The Free Press, 38&ndash;94.</li>

<li>Syros, Vasileios, 2006, &ldquo;The Sovereignty of the Multitude in
the Works of Marsilius of Padua, Peter of Auvergne, and Some Other
Aristotelian Commentators&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#MR2006">Moreno-Ria&ntilde;o 2006</a>:
 227&ndash;248. doi:10.1484/M.DISPUT-EB.3.443</li>

<li id="Syros2011">&ndash;&ndash;&ndash; (ed.), 2011a, <em>Well Begun
Is Only Half Done: Tracing Aristotle&rsquo;s Political Ideas in
Medieval Arabic, Syriac, Byzantine, and Jewish Sources</em> (Medieval
and Renaissance Texts and Studies 388), Tempe, AZ: ACMRS (Arizona
Center for Medieval and Renaissance Studies).</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2011b, &ldquo;Did the Physician from Padua
Meet the Rabbi from Cordoba? Marsilius of Padua and Moses Maimonides
on the Political Utility of Religion&rdquo;, <em>Revue des
&eacute;tudes juives</em>, 170(1): 51&ndash;71.
doi:10.2143/REJ.170.1.2126640</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2012, <em>Marsilius of Padua at the
Intersection of Ancient and Medieval Traditions of Political
Thought</em>, Toronto: University of Toronto Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2020, &ldquo;Marsilius of Padua and Isaac
Abravanel on Kingship: The Medieval Precedents of Republicanism
Revisited&rdquo;, <em>Medieval Encounters</em>, 26(3): 203&ndash;225.
doi:10.1163/15700674-12340071</li>

<li>Tabarroni, Andrea, 2019, &ldquo;Dante et Marsile&#8239;: deux
voies &agrave; la naturalisation de la politique&rdquo;, Andrea
Bruschi (trans.), in
 <a href="#LBR2019">de Libera, Brenet, and Rosier-Catach 2019</a>:
 385&ndash;402. doi:10.4000/books.lesbelleslettres.478</li>

<li>Tierney, Brian, 1979, &ldquo;Aristotle, Aquinas, and the Ideal
Constitution&rdquo;, <em>Proceedings of the PMR Conference 4</em>,
1&ndash;11.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1982, <em>Religion, Law and the Growth of
Constitutional Thought 1150&ndash;1650</em>, Cambridge, Cambridge
University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1987, &ldquo;Hierarchy, Consent, and the
&lsquo;Western Tradition&rsquo;&rdquo;, <em>Political Theory</em>,
15(4): 646&ndash;652. doi:10.1177/0090591787015004009</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1997, <em>The Idea of Natural Rights:
Studies on Natural Rights, Natural Law, and Church Law,
1150&ndash;1625</em>, Atlanta, GA: Scholars Press.</li>

<li>Toivanen, Juhana, 2021, <em>The Political Animal in Medieval
Philosophy: A Philosophical Study of the Commentary Tradition,
c.1260&ndash;c.1410</em> (Studien und texte zur Geistesgeschichte des
Mittelalters, Band 129), Leiden: Brill. doi:10.1163/9789004438460</li>

<li>Toste, Marco, 2020, &ldquo;The Parts and the Whole, the Few Wise
Men and the Multitude. Consent and Collective Decision Making in Two
Medieval Commentaries on Aristotle&rsquo;s
&lsquo;Politics&rsquo;&rdquo;, <em>Storia del pensiero politico</em>,
9(2): 209&ndash;232. doi:10.4479/98339</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2022, &ldquo;Introduction&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#questiones">Petrus de Alvernia [Peter of Auvergne] <em>Questiones</em></a>:
 3&ndash;48.</li>

<li>Tuck, Richard, 1979, <em>Natural Rights Theories: Their Origin and
Development</em>, Cambridge/New York: Cambridge University Press.
doi:10.1017/CBO9781139163569</li>

<li>Ubl, Karl, 2003, &ldquo;Johannes Quidorts Weg zur
Sozialphilosophie&rdquo;, <em>Francia. Forschungen zur
westeurop&auml;ischen Geschichte</em>, 30(1): 43&ndash;72.
doi:10.11588/FR.2003.1.45435</li>

<li>Vatter, Miguel, 2020, &ldquo;Dignity and the Foundation of Human
Rights: Toward an Averroist Genealogy&rdquo;, <em>Politics and
Religion</em>, 13(2): 304&ndash;332.
doi:10.1017/S1755048319000336</li>

<li>Villey, Michel, 1968, <em>La formation de la pens&eacute;e
juridique moderne</em>, 1st edition, Paris: Montchrestien.</li>

<li>Willard, Charity Cannon, 1984, <em>Christine de Pizan: Her Life
and Works</em>, New York: Persea Books.</li>

<li>Woerther, Fr&eacute;d&eacute;rique, 2011, &ldquo;La
<em>Rh&eacute;torique</em> d&rsquo;Aristote comme moyen de diffusion
des id&eacute;es politiques aristot&eacute;liciennes dans la
philosophie politique arabe: Les <em>Didascalia Rhetoricam ex glosa
Alpharabii</em>&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#Syros2011">Syros 2011</a>:
 49&ndash;71.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2018, &ldquo;Averroes&rsquo; Goals in the
Paraphrase (Middle Commentary) of Aristotle&rsquo;s <em>Nicomachean
Ethics</em>&rdquo;, in <em>Interpreting Averroes: Critical
Essays</em>, Peter Adamson and Matteo Di Giovanni (eds.), Cambridge:
Cambridge University Press, 218&ndash;236 (ch. 12).
doi:10.1017/9781316335543.013</li>

<li>Woodhouse, Adam, 2017, &ldquo;&lsquo;Who Owns the Money?&rsquo;
Currency, Property, and Popular Sovereignty in Nicole Oresme&rsquo;s
<em>De moneta</em>&rdquo;, <em>Speculum</em>, 92(1): 85&ndash;116.
doi:10.1086/689839</li>
</ul>
</div> 

